# CC PROMPT — v2.35.8 — Five new high-value non-destructive task templates

## What this does

Adds five new read-only task templates covering operational gaps the current
TaskTemplates catalogue doesn't address. Each template exercises tools that
already exist in the agent allowlist — no new tool capabilities required.

New templates:

1. **Container restart loop diagnosis** (INFRASTRUCTURE group, non-destructive)
   — finds containers that are flapping (exit codes, restart counts,
   last_exit_time, recent logs around each restart).
2. **Certificate expiry check** (SECURITY group, non-destructive) —
   inventories SSL cert expiry across reverse proxies and flags anything
   <30 days from expiry.
3. **DNS resolver consistency** (NETWORK group, non-destructive) — checks
   that all configured DNS servers resolve the same core records (split-brain
   detection).
4. **Docker overlay network health** (SWARM group, non-destructive) —
   enumerates Swarm overlay networks, checks ingress reachability from every
   worker, flags orphaned or unused networks.
5. **Agent success rate audit** (new PLATFORM group, non-destructive) — the
   agent reflects on itself: queries `/api/logs/operations?limit=100`, groups
   by agent_type and status, reports completion rate + top-failing task
   patterns in the last week.

Version bump: 2.35.7 → 2.35.8.

